          "date": "2013-04-05 00:06:38.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-3093 lnet: Fix lnet selftest crash",
        "message": "LU-3093 lnet: Fix lnet selftest crash\n\nWhen adding a group using lst add_group the group is added if and\nonly if at least one node is added successfully in the group.  There\nare two cases that has to be handled:\n\n1. An invlaid NID is provided, in which case the code still created\nan empty group, but come time the group is used in a test, an assert\nwhich checks that there is at least one node in the group is hit and\nthe entire operating system crashes.  Ideally there should be no\nassertion on user input.\n\n2. A valid NID is provided but the NID is not reachable.  In this cae\nthe node is added in UNKNOWN state, and test still doesn't run\nsuccessfully.\n\nThe fix is to ensure that a group has at least one acive node.\nAn addition of a non-empty group will not be supported.  Thus the\nassert will never be hit.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I599c6351ac9aab4cc64a29f9f527cc1cfffaaecb\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
